    "## 7. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)\n",
    "\n",
    "In this section, we perform exploratory data analysis to understand patterns, trends, and relationships within the Zomato dataset.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### 7.1 Rating Distribution\n",
    "\n",
    "This analysis shows how restaurant ratings are distributed across the dataset. Most restaurants fall within the 3–4 rating range, indicating average to good performance.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### 7.2 Cost Distribution\n",
    "\n",
    "This section analyzes the distribution of restaurant pricing. It helps identify whether most restaurants are budget-friendly or expensive.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### 7.3 Cost vs Rating\n",
    "\n",
    "This analysis examines the relationship between cost and rating. It helps determine whether higher-priced restaurants provide better quality or customer satisfaction.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### 7.4 Top Locations\n",
    "\n",
    "This section identifies locations with the highest number of restaurants. It highlights popular food hubs and high-demand areas.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### 7.5 Restaurant Type Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "This analysis focuses on different types of restaurants such as cafes, casual dining, and quick bites. It helps understand which types are most common and their performance.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### 7.6 Online Order Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "This section compares restaurants that offer online ordering with those that do not. It helps understand its impact on ratings and customer engagement.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### 7.7 Votes vs Rating\n",
    "\n",
    "This analysis explores the relationship between the number of votes and ratings. Generally, restaurants with more votes tend to have higher credibility and better ratings.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
